sql:
SELECT soil_id, AVG(whc) AS average_water_holding_capacity, AVG(precipitation) AS average_precipitation
FROM environmental_conditions
GROUP BY soil_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'Agronomy' is a branch of agriculture that deals with the science of soil management and crop production;
- 'Growth cycle' refers to the time it takes for a crop to mature from planting to harvest;
- 'Precipitation' is the amount of water falling in the form of rain, snow, sleet, or hail.

- 'Significantly high precipitation' refers to more than 659 mm;
- 'Warm minimum temperature' refers to more than 22°C;
- 'Ample sunlight' refers to more than 7 hours per day on average;
- The final conditions also require an average precipitation of more than 600 mm and average sunlight hours of more than 8 hours.
